    "In general, at a given epoch, the smallest region will be more affected than more extended regions foot_10 This basic rule helps to anticipate the shape of a spectral deformation.",
    "The simplest diagnostic for the presence of microlensing in spectra consists of calculating spectral ratios between pairs of gravitationally lensed images (see also Fig. 19).",
    "Let us consider the spectra of two lensed images of an AGN, F 1 (λ) and F 2 (λ), as observed in the optical rest-frame range at two epochs separated by the time delay.",
    "In absence of microlensing, those two images are simply magnified by the macro-magnification M 1 and M 2.",
